# gen124 (discovery-harness pull): casual small-talk phrasings the chatsim
# transcripts (tests/chat/sim/) kept walling on. These are phatic contact, not
# information requests, so they belong to the social register (mod_social) — and
# the fix is DATA: new social_pattern facts in knowledge/social.pl, matched
# against the canonicalized text. No C change beyond the version bump. Held-out:
# any phrasing carrying one of these cues lands, not just these exact lines.

# "what's up" and its contraction-expanded twin "whats up" -> what is up.
> what's up?
< I'm well, thanks. How can I help?
> whats up
< I'm well, thanks. How can I help?
> wassup
< I'm well, thanks. How can I help?

# "you good" / "u good" — a wellbeing check in chat shorthand.
> you good?
< I'm well, thanks. How can I help?
> u good
< I'm well, thanks. How can I help?

# "you there?" is phatic presence-contact -> a greeting, not a wall.
> you there?
< Hi there!

# Anti-impostor: a real world-knowledge question parrot0 wasn't taught still gets
# the honest wall — small-talk patterns must not swallow genuine questions.
> is the sky blue?
< I don't understand that yet.
